latestPosts.caption:
These days, mall shopping is quick, easy, and under the comfort of AC but nothing beats the feel of those old city market strolls.
As a child, I remember the excitement of going with my mom, picking fabrics, matching bangles, juttis, that one special outfit for Eid or a wedding 💫 
I wanted my daughters to feel that same magic ✨
So off we went to the bylanes of the old city 😍
From buying fabric for their Eid outfits (before the @rawish_designs tailors get overbooked 😅), to bangle matching, jutti hunting, having Kaladi Kulcha, and sipping Banta from the iconic Bantawala 🥛
And of course, ending the day with the legendary Falooda Kulfi 😋

It wasn’t just shopping — it was a day full of stories, laughter, flavours, and those little traditions I grew up with.
A day I’ll always remember… and I hope they will too 🤍

#NostalgiaTrip #EidPrep #OldCityFeels #MakingMemories #ᴇɪᴅ2025 #motherdaughters #eidshopping

Went jewellery shopping with the lil one today!

Honestly, it turned into the best mom-daughter date I could’ve asked for.

She’s already such a little diva — so sure of what she likes (and doesn’t!), picking out “the sparkly ones” like a pro and even giving me style tips.

Silverlines made sure we both walked out with pieces we both loved. So many options, and so many exquisite designs.

And the best part? A special memory I’ll keep forever.

#Silverlines #MotherDaughter #forevermemory #jewellery #gold

Took my 5.5 year-old triplets and my 4-year-old for their first go-karting ride at Kartomania and they had the time of their lives😍
The team was amazing, not only experienced but also super child-friendly. They have a dedicated briefing area where they guide kids (and adults) on what to do and all the safety measures to follow before the ride 💫
If you’re looking for something different and exciting to do with your little ones, this is a must-try🤩

Save this for your next weekend plan❤️

📍Entertainment Mall Sector 83 Gurgaon
